
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `enchant-lsmod-2` list module haaye Enchant raa neshon midehad.  Enchant yek ketabkhane ast baraye spell checking, va in dastoor be shoma komak mikonad module haaye fa'al Enchant raa bebinid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `enchant-lsmod-2` --> 📜 List hameye module haaye Enchant e mojood va fa'al.
    🔹 `enchant-lsmod-2 -v` --> 👀 Namayesh etela'at bishtar darbareye module haa.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ enchant-lsmod-2

    🔹 Namayesh list sade module haa

    $ enchant-lsmod-2 -v

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at kamel module haa

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ enchant-lsmod-2
    ispell
    myspell
    hunspell

    🔹 Module haaye `ispell`, `myspell`, va `hunspell` fa'al hastand va Enchant az anha baraye spell checking estefade mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `enchant-lsmod-2` command lists the available Enchant modules.  Enchant is a library for spell checking, and this command helps you see which modules are currently enabled.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `enchant-lsmod-2` --> 📜 List all available and enabled Enchant modules.
    🔹 `enchant-lsmod-2 -v` --> 👀 Display more detailed information about the modules.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ enchant-lsmod-2

    🔹 Displays a simple list of modules.

    $ enchant-lsmod-2 -v

    🔹 Displays more complete information for each module.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ enchant-lsmod-2
    ispell
    myspell
    hunspell

    🔹 The `ispell`, `myspell`, and `hunspell` modules are enabled, and Enchant uses them for spell checking.

